3. **First Fit**: No priority; choose the first bin that can fit the item.
4. **Best Fit**: Choose the bin where the item fits best, i.e., the remaining space is as close as possible to the item size.
5. **Worst Fit**: Choose the bin where the item fits the worst, i.e., the remaining space is as large as possible.
6. **Most Full Bins First**: Higher priority to bins that are already more full.
7. **Least Full Bins First**: Higher priority to bins that are less full.
8. **Variance Minimization**: Choose bins where adding the item would minimize the variance of bin sizes.
9. **Similarity Heuristic**: Choose bins where the average size of items is similar to the new item.
10. **Combination Heuristics**: Combine multiple of the above heuristics.

